.TH "get_slot_mapping" 9 "get_slot_mapping" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_slot_mapping \- determine logical slot mapping for PCI device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" get_slot_mapping
.BI "(struct pci_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "u8 bus_num "  ","
.BI "u8 dev_num "  ","
.BI "u8 *slot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "bus_num" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "dev_num" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "slot" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Won't work for more than one PCI-PCI bridge in a slot.

\fIbus_num\fP - bus number of PCI device
\fIdev_num\fP - device number of PCI device
\fIslot\fP - Pointer to u8 where slot number will be returned

Output:      SUCCESS or FAILURE
